claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: Flowchart showing the primary analysis cohorts with participant numbers for recombinant quadrivalent influenza vaccine (RIV4, n=3,047), standard dose influenza vaccine (SD-IIV4, n=862), and unvaccinated groups (n=8,878 for one cohort and n=1,398 for another), along with a note that 5,136 participants were included. does not support the claim because the image only presents participant group sizes and study cohort flow; it does not provide any information on antigenic matching with WHO- or FDA-selected strains.
